# Summary of timelines

* . . .

* The price of Enron’s stock was influenced by reported revenue, earnings, debts, cash flow, growth potential, etc.

* In late 1990, Enron controlled about 25% of all electricity and natural gas contracts traded worldwide.

* On 28 December 2000, the 7th most valuable and largest corporation in the United States (Enron shares: US$84.87).

* 28 November 2001, Enron shares plunged below US$1.

* Filed bankruptcy on 2 Dec 2001 (20,000 employees; $618 million loss; eliminating US$1.2 billion of shareholder equity).

