# Serious Fraud Office

* In 1983, the Fraud Trials Committee was set up to consider the introduction of more effective means of fighting fraud (commonly known as The Roskill Committee, the Roskill Report)

* Created by the Criminal Justice Act 1987;

* An independent governmental department that had both investigative and prosecutorial powers (cooperation and interchange of information amongst law enforcement authorities were inefficient and unsatisfactory).

* (In September 2007, in the midst of criticism of SFO, the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) created the Fraud Prosecution Unit (now called Fraud Prosecution Division)).

