# Replacement of Turnbull Guidance

* Corporate failures in 2001 in the US revealed some loopholes in corporate governance. The UK responded by the creation of the Higgs Committee (in relation to role and effectiveness of non-executive directors) and the Smith Committee (in relation to audit committee in a company) in 2002. (not mentioned in Chapter 6)

* Both reports of Higgs and Smith recommended a revision of the Combined Code. (not mentioned in Chapter 6)

* In 2003, the new Combined Code was published. (not mentioned in Chapter 6)

